# Getting Started

Ethereum, since its inception, has established itself as a leading platform for decentralized applications (dApps) and smart contracts. However, its growth and widespread adoption have brought to light several scalability issues that impact its efficiency and usability. Optimism, like many blockchain technologies, is in a state of continual evolution, constantly seeking to refine its technology and add new features. This ongoing development is crucial in addressing the ever-evolving demands of the blockchain sector. Here, we expand on these challenges. 
